<span class=pageheading>5 Things to Understand About Title Insurance</SPAN><br><br>

<ol class=text>
<li>It protects your ownership right to your home both
from fraudulent claims against your ownership and from mistakes made in earlier
sales, such as mistake in the spelling of a person’s name or an inaccurate
description of the property.</li>

<li>It’s a one-time cost usually based on the price of the
property.</li>

<li>It’s usually paid for by the sellers.</li>

<li>There are both lender title policies, which protect
the lender, and owner title policies, which protect you. The lender will
probably require a lender policy.</li>

<li>Discounts on premiums are sometimes available if the
home has been bought within only a few years since not as much work is required
to check the title. Ask the title company if this discount is available.</li>
</ol>

